question.title: JNDI Lookup Failing with Default Settings
question.body:
I'm trying to implement a basic database web application in Netbeans using Java Server Faces and a Java Database. But whenever I try to deploy the application, I get the following error message:

Exception while deploying the app [Vehicles_of_Interest_Web] : JNDI lookup failed for the resource: Name: [Vehicles_of_Interest_WebPU], Lookup: [jdbc:derby://localhost:1527/VehiclesOfInterest [VehiclesOfInterest on VEHICLESOFINTEREST]], Type: [javax.sql.DataSource]

I'm using Netbeans 26 and Glassfish 8.0. My process for creating the code was creating a database in Javascript, creating a web application via Java w/ Ant, selecting JavaScript Faces as a framework, and Glassfish 8.0 as my server. I then generated classes by going to new -> Java w/ Ant -> Persistence -> Entity Classes from Database, importing all tables. Then I generated pages using new -> Java w/ Ant -> Persistence -> JSF Pages for Entity Classes, again importing all entities. When I attempt to deploy the application I get the above error.

I've been looking into all of the configuration files, to see if the lookup name was inconsistent with the database name, but everything looks consistent. I've also tried to create a new file, but the same problem arises. I'm new to working with configuration files, so please be very explicit in any answer that covers them.

The text of my config files:

    <jta-data-source>jdbc:derby://localhost:1527/VehiclesOfInterest [VehiclesOfInterest on VEHICLESOFINTEREST]</jta-data-source>
    <class>model.VehicleOfInterest</class>
    <exclude-unlisted-classes>false</exclude-unlisted-classes>
    <properties/>
  </persistence-unit>
</persistence>

web.xml

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<web-app version="5.0" xmlns="https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_5_0.xsd">
    <context-param>

        <param-value>Development</param-value>
    </context-param>
    <servlet>
        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>
        <servlet-class>jakarta.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>
        <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>
    </servlet>
    <servlet-mapping>

    </servlet-mapping>
    <welcome-file-list>

    </welcome-file-list>
</web-app>
